gomodel:SYNGO_3987  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: localization by immunogold electron microscopy to post-synaptic spines, away from the membrane at filamentous actin branch points. Although no validation by KO exists, a western blot showing the antibody recognizes a single band with the relevant antibody used for staining is included in the supplement.\n\n29/01/2021 Dnyanada: The paper demonstrates antibody specificity.\nLiteral:\n\"The primary antibody was a polyclonal rabbit anti-ARPC-2 (also called p34 in mammals, and arc35 in yeast) generated against a peptide corresponding to amino acids 285-298 of human ARPC-2 (Upstate Biotechnology #07-227). This widely used antibody has been well characterized (Di Nardo et al., 2005; Kempiak et al., 2005; Hotulainen and Lappalainen, 2006). Western blot analysis confirmed that the antibody recognizes a single band in rat brain homogenate, migrating at ~34 kDa (supplemental Fig. 1, available at www.jneurosci.org as supplemental material).\". Experimental description: Experiments were performed on adult Sprague Dawley rats" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3987" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

